verbose_text: XREF_BIBR The complex process of carcinogenesis involves several stages, that can be summarized as follows : endogenous hyperinsulinemia (insulin resistance), exogenous hyperinsulinemia (treatment with insulin or secretagogues), hyperglycemia, increased proinflammatory state and oxidative stress make damage to the genetic code more likely, increased angiogenesis and cell proliferation and reduced apoptosis rate.
